<node id="Mrs. Cratchit">
  <data key="d0">Mrs. Cratchit</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Mrs. Cratchit is the wife of Bob Cratchit, contributing to the family dynamic portrayed in "A Christmas Carol."&lt;SEP&gt;Mrs. Cratchit is Bob Cratchit's wife, characterized by her caring nature and her efforts to manage the family's meager resources.&lt;SEP&gt;Mrs. Cratchit is Bob's wife, who prepares the family's Christmas dinner and expresses nervousness about the pudding.&lt;SEP&gt;Mrs. Cratchit is a character known for her pride in the pudding she made and her strong feelings toward Mr. Scrooge.&lt;SEP&gt;Mrs. Cratchit is the mother of the Cratchit Family, depicted as industrious and caring towards her children and husband.&lt;SEP&gt;Mrs. Cratchit is a character who expresses positive sentiments about another person and engages in conversations with her family.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1932e9b8ed52abe1ef474137263a18e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-392109aa88dfa4908b740d7d5ae9eb90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e38b901b0e466ddad5ceba76c831be45&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d1e2aab497ed7790d901896ad101170b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-363439bcd624e1e2a87ae3085ee58234&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9856cf623e8bc291b045f847afe980d4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
