<node id="The Ghost">
  <data key="d0">The Ghost</data>
  <data key="d1">creature</data>
  <data key="d2">The Ghost is a transparent apparition of Jacob Marley, who is burdened with chains and seeks to communicate with Scrooge.&lt;SEP&gt;The Ghost is an ethereal presence in Scrooge's life, symbolizing his fears and contemplation about the consequences of his actions.&lt;SEP&gt;The Ghost is a supernatural being that interacts with Scrooge, reminding him of his past and the people in his life.&lt;SEP&gt;The Ghost is a spectral figure that interacts with Scrooge, prompting him to reflect on his past memories and emotions.&lt;SEP&gt;The Ghost is a spirit that observes Scrooge during the dance, prompting reflection on the power of joy and gratitude.&lt;SEP&gt;The Ghost is a supernatural entity that serves as a moral guide for Scrooge, challenging his views on life and existence.&lt;SEP&gt;The Ghost is a spectral being that reveals significant scenes related to death and invokes deep emotions in Scrooge.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-928dd8a9f2ac4eca27f7236059c6d549&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fba42af86ca95063ecb2c8150196ec9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20fceefa1e94928dd83195b2e5c0ed99&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d1e2aab497ed7790d901896ad101170b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe4a986f2389404ae0ec7987afdbfb72&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cc8f8613a09cf229c18602a9ca1f075&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7ed2fe52b532c703dc5c1cf4927f87d</data>
