<node id="Jacob Marley">
  <data key="d0">Jacob Marley</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Jacob Marley is the deceased business partner of Scrooge, whose spirit appears as a Ghost to warn and guide Scrooge about his past actions.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacob Marley is a ghostly figure who claims to be the partner of Scrooge and appears to him in a spectral form.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacob Marley is a deceased character who appears as a Ghost to warn Scrooge about his past misdeeds and future consequences.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacob Marley is Scrooge's deceased business partner who sends the Ghost to warn Scrooge of his ways.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacob Marley is a character who has passed away and is referenced in connection with Scrooge's reflections on life and death.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacob Marley is a deceased character whose prediction about Scrooge influences his interactions with the spirits.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacob Marley is a spirit and former business partner of Scrooge, representing the consequences of a life lived without compassion.</data>
